<section id="itsm_mtConfidence">
    <title>mtConfidence</title>
    
    <para>Machine Translation Confidence - the <code>mtConfidence</code> attribute is the <olink
            targetdoc="../xliff21.xml" targetptr="ITS20">[ITS]</olink> defined
            <code>mtConfidence</code> attribute.</para>
    
    
    <para><emphasis>Value description:</emphasis> floating point number between 0 and 1.</para>
    <para>The number represents the self reported confidence of the application or service providing
        the <ulink url="http://www.w3.org/TR/its20/#mtconfidence">MT Confidence</ulink> metadata, the higher the better.</para>
    
    <para><emphasis>Default value:</emphasis>: undefined</para>
    
    
    
    <para><emphasis>Used in:</emphasis>
        <olink targetdoc="../../elements/inline/mrk.xml" targetptr="mrk"
            ><code>&lt;mrk></code></olink>, and
        <olink targetdoc="../../elements/inline/sm.xml"
            targetptr="sm"><code>&lt;sm></code></olink>.</para>
    
    <itemizedlist>
        <title>Constraints</title>
        <listitem><para>When the attribute <link linkend="itsm_mtConfidence"><code>mtConfidence</code></link> is
                set, the element where it is set <glossterm>must</glossterm> be in the scope of an
                    <olink targetdoc="itsm_annotatorsRef.xml" targetptr="itsm_annotatorsRef"
                        ><code>annotatorsRef</code></olink> attribute with the <olink targetdoc="../../xliff21.xml" targetptr="ITS20">[ITS]</olink><ulink url="https://www.w3.org/TR/its20/#datacategories-overview"
                            >Data category
                            identifier</ulink> part of exactly one list value equal to the string
                    <code>mt-confidence</code>.</para></listitem>
    </itemizedlist>
    <para>See the <olink targetdoc="../../modules/itsm/MT_Confidence.xml" targetptr="MTConfidenceAnnotation">ITS MT Confidence Annotation</olink> for the full normative usage description of this attribute. Other advanced Constraints follow from that normative usage description.</para>
    <itemizedlist>
        <title>Processing Requirements</title>
        <listitem>
            <para><firstterm>Writers</firstterm>
                <glossterm>must</glossterm> use the <olink
                    targetdoc="../candidates/matchQuality.xml" targetptr="matchQuality"
                        ><code>mtc:matchQuality</code></olink> attribute to express the <link
                    linkend="itsm_mtConfidence"><code>MTConfidence</code></link> attribute on an
                    <olink targetdoc="../../elements/candidates/match.xml" targetptr="match"
                        ><code>&lt;mtc:match></code></olink> element.</para>
            <itemizedlist>
                <listitem>
                    <para>The floating point number between 0 and 1 <glossterm>must</glossterm> be expressed as
                        a decimal number between 0.0 and 100.0 [%].</para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>The <olink
                        targetdoc="../candidates/matchQuality.xml" targetptr="matchQuality"
                        ><code>mtc:matchQuality</code></olink> attribute  used by the <firstterm>Writer</firstterm> to express the <link
                            linkend="itsm_mtConfidence"><code>MTConfidence</code></link> attribute <glossterm>must</glossterm> be in scope of an <olink targetdoc="../../attributes/itsm/itsm_annotatorsRef.xml" targetptr="itsm_annotatorsRef"><code>annotatorsRef</code></olink> attribute with the <olink targetdoc="../../xliff21.xml" targetptr="ITS20">[ITS]</olink><ulink url="https://www.w3.org/TR/its20/#datacategories-overview"
                                >Data category
                                identifier</ulink> part of exactly one list value equal to the string
                        <code>mt-confidence</code>.</para>
                </listitem>
            </itemizedlist>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para><firstterm>Modifiers</firstterm>
                <glossterm>may</glossterm> use this <link linkend="itsm_mtConfidence"
                        ><code>MTConfidence</code></link> attribute, when populating the
                    <firstterm>XLIFF Core</firstterm>
                <olink targetdoc="../../structural/target.xml" targetptr="target"
                        ><code>&lt;target></code></olink> elements with exact unmodified MT matches
                from <olink targetdoc="../../elements/candidates/match.xml" targetptr="match"
                        ><code>&lt;mtc:match></code></olink> elements with the <olink
                    targetdoc="../candidates/matchQuality.xml" targetptr="matchQuality"
                        ><code>mtc:matchQuality</code></olink> attribute set and in scope of an
                    <olink targetdoc="../../attributes/itsm/itsm_annotatorsRef.xml"
                    targetptr="itsm_annotatorsRef"><code>annotatorsRef</code></olink> attribute with
                the <olink targetdoc="../../xliff21.xml" targetptr="ITS20">[ITS]</olink><ulink url="https://www.w3.org/TR/its20/#datacategories-overview"
                    >Data category
                    identifier</ulink> part of exactly one list value equal to the string
                    <code>mt-confidence</code>.</para>
            <itemizedlist>
                <listitem>
                    <para>The decimal number between 0.0 and 100.0 [%] <glossterm>must</glossterm> be expressed as
                        a floating point number between 0 and 1.</para>
                </listitem>
            </itemizedlist>
        </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>
    
</section>
